    <h1 class="Headers"> Theories of Behaviour </h1>

    <h2 class="Headers"> ABC Theory of Attitude and Behaviour </h2>
    <p class="Content"> The ABC Theory states that behaviour and <br>
     behavioral change is comprised of three things....
    <br>
    <br>

      Parts that make up behaviour <br>
     1. Affective (Emotion) <br>
     2. Behavioral (Your tendencies) <br>
     3. Cognitive (Attitude or what you think of it)


</p>


    <h2 class="Headers"> Theory of Planned Behaviour </h2>
    <p> Theory of Planned Behaviour states that <br>
    behaviour is based on three things
    </p>
    <ol> Parts that dictate behaviour
    <li> Attitude </li>
    <li> Subjective norms </li>
    <li> How much you think you can control your behaviour </li>
  </ol>

    <h2 class="Headers"> Attitude-Behaviour Theory </h2>
    <p> Attitude-Behaviour Theory states that <br>
    behaviour is based on your attitude and some <br>
    extra knowledge. An event in your past life <br>
    causes you to form an attitude toward some <br>
    behaviour, and with addition to some knowledge <br>
    your own behaviour will be formed.
    </p>

    <h2 class="Headers"> Prototype Theory of Behaviour </h2>
    <p> The Prototype Theory of Behaviour states that <br>
    behaviour is based on many things such as.....
    </p>
    <ol> PASOOP
    <li> Past Behaviour </li>
    <li> Attitude </li>
    <li> Subjective norms</li>
    <li> Own Willingness </li>
    <li> Own Intentions </li>
    <li> Prototype or model we look up to </li>
  </ol>





